    <div xml:id="PN362">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ñāyiṟ ṟaṉṉa vāymaṇi miṭainta</l>
<l>matiyuṟa ḻāra mārpiṟ puraḷap</l>
<l>palipeṟu muracam pācaṟaic cilaippap</l>
<l>poḻilakam paranta pe<gap quantity="32" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="25" reason="lost" unit="character"/>kuma vicaya veṇkoṭi</l>
<l>yaṇaṅkurut taṉṉa kaṇaṅkoṭ ṭāṉaik</l>
<l>kūṟṟat taṉṉa māṟṟaru muṉpi</l>
<l>ṉākkuraṟ kāṇpi ṉanta ṇāḷir</l>
<l>nāṉmaṟai kuṟi<gap quantity="35" reason="lost" unit="character"/>yi</l>
<l>ṉaṟaṅkuṟit taṉṟu poruḷā kutaliṉ</l>
<l>maruṭīrntu mayakkorīik</l>
<l>kaipeytanīr kaṭaṟparappa</l>
<l>vāmirunta vaṭainalkic</l>
<l>cōṟukoṭuttu mikaperitum</l>
<l>vīṟucāṉ <gap quantity="21" reason="lost" unit="character"/> naṉṟuñ</l>
<l>ciṟuveḷ ḷeṉpi ṉeṭuveṇ kaḷariṉ</l>
<l>vāyvaṉ kākkai kūkaiyoṭu kūṭip</l>
<l>pakaluṅ kūvu makalu ḷāṅkaṭ</l>
<l>kāṭukaṇ maṟaitta kalleṉ cuṟṟamō</l>
<l>ṭilleṉ ṟilvayiṟ peyara mella</l>
<l>viṭañciṟi totuṅka lañci</l>
<l>yuṭampoṭuñ ceṉmā ruyarntōr nāṭṭē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While moon-like pearl-strings roll on [his] chest (2)</l>
<l>that are set close with sun-like choice gems, (1) </l>
<l>while in the warcamp the offering-receiving drum resounds, (3)</l>
<l>that spreads in the grove……………… (4)</l>
<l>white victory banners…………………. (5)</l>
<l>a grouped army that takes shape like Aṇaṅkus, (6)</l>
<l>with a strength difficult to sway that is like [that of] Death, (7)</l>
<l>you brahmin men with the sight [and] cow voices, (8)</l>
<l>the sign of the four Vedas……………. (9)</l>
<l>virtue is intended. Because that is wealth, (10)</l>
<l>ending delusion, dispelling confusion, (11)</l>
<l>grating villages(?) that are by the water (13)</l>
<l>while an ocean of water poured by hand spreads, (12)</l>
<l>giving rice, much and a lot, (14)</l>
<l>abounding in excellence………..good (15)</l>
<l>– in order to go, along with the body, to the land of the high-born(?), (21)</l>
<l>afraid of stepping aside a little from the place, (20)</l>
<l>softly, while moving from the house, saying “no”, (19)</l>
<l>along with the noisy retinue that hides the space of the wilderness/cremation ground, (18)</l>
<l>there in the width, where they shriek even by day: (17)</l>
<l>the beak-strong crows along with the owls, gathering, (16)</l>
<l>in the large white saline soil with little white bones. (15)</l>
</lg>
